  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Heat a <span class=\"text-highlight\">large,</span> wide-based pan<span class=\"text-highlight\"> (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid)</span> with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium-low heat </p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>red onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10-15 min or until softened and caramelised </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left <span class=\"text-highlight\">with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> thinner pieces</span></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced chicken</strong> to a baking tray </p>\n<p>Drizzle with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 15-20 min or until the <strong>chicken </strong>is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> with the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong> and <strong>chopped chives</strong> in a small bowl</p>\n<p>Add a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>ranch-style dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1719.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
